#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:3
msgid "Dealing with the file system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:5
msgid ""
"Pyodide includes a file system provided by Emscripten. In JavaScript, the "
"Pyodide file system can be accessed through {js:attr}`pyodide.FS` which re-"
"exports the [Emscripten File System API](https://emscripten.org/docs/"
"api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#filesystem-api)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:10
msgid "**Example: Reading from the file system**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:12
msgid ""
"pyodide.runPython(`\n"
"  from pathlib import Path\n"
"\n"
"  Path(\"/hello.txt\").write_text(\"hello world!\")\n"
"`);\n"
"\n"
"let file = pyodide.FS.readFile(\"/hello.txt\", { encoding: \"utf8\" });\n"
"console.log(file); // ==> \"hello world!\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:23
msgid "**Example: Writing to the file system**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:25
msgid ""
"let data = \"hello world!\";\n"
"pyodide.FS.writeFile(\"/hello.txt\", data, { encoding: \"utf8\" });\n"
"pyodide.runPython(`\n"
"  from pathlib import Path\n"
"\n"
"  print(Path(\"/hello.txt\").read_text())\n"
"`);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:35
msgid "Mounting a file system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:37
msgid ""
"The default file system used in Pyodide is [MEMFS](https://emscripten.org/"
"docs/api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#memfs), which is a virtual in-memory "
"file system. The data stored in MEMFS will be lost when the page is reloaded."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:40
msgid ""
"If you wish for files to persist, you can mount other file systems. Other "
"file systems provided by Emscripten are `IDBFS`, `NODEFS`, `PROXYFS`, "
"`WORKERFS`. Note that some filesystems can only be used in specific runtime "
"environments. See [Emscripten File System API](https://emscripten.org/docs/"
"api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#filesystem-api) for more details. For "
"instance, to store data persistently between page reloads, one could mount a "
"folder with the [IDBFS file system](https://emscripten.org/docs/"
"api_reference/Filesystem-API.html#filesystem-api-idbfs)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:48
msgid ""
"let mountDir = \"/mnt\";\n"
"pyodide.FS.mkdirTree(mountDir);\n"
"pyodide.FS.mount(pyodide.FS.filesystems.IDBFS, {}, mountDir);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:54
msgid ""
"If you are using Node.js you can access the native file system by mounting "
"`NODEFS`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:56
msgid ""
"let mountDir = \"/mnt\";\n"
"pyodide.FS.mkdirTree(mountDir);\n"
"pyodide.FS.mount(pyodide.FS.filesystems.NODEFS, { root: \".\" }, mountDir);\n"
"pyodide.runPython(\"import os; print(os.listdir('/mnt'))\");\n"
"// ==> The list of files in the Node working directory\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:66
msgid "(Experimental) Using the native file system in the browser"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:68
msgid ""
"You can access the native file system from the browser using the [File "
"System Access API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/"
"File_System_Access_API)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:71
msgid "This is experimental"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:74
msgid ""
"The File System Access API is only supported in Chromium based browsers: "
"Chrome and Edge (as of 2022/08/18)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:77
msgid "Mounting a directory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:79
msgid ""
"Pyodide provides an API {js:func}`pyodide.mountNativeFS` which mounts a {js:"
"class}`FileSystemDirectoryHandle` into the Pyodide Python file system."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:82
msgid ""
"const dirHandle = await showDirectoryPicker();\n"
"const permissionStatus = await dirHandle.requestPermission({\n"
"  mode: \"readwrite\",\n"
"});\n"
"\n"
"if (permissionStatus !== \"granted\") {\n"
"  throw new Error(\"readwrite access to directory not granted\");\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"const nativefs = await pyodide.mountNativeFS(\"/mount_dir\", dirHandle);\n"
"\n"
"pyodide.runPython(`\n"
"  import os\n"
"  print(os.listdir('/mount_dir'))\n"
"`);\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:100
msgid "Synchronizing changes to native file system"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:102
msgid ""
"Due to browser limitations, the changes in the mounted file system is not "
"synchronized by default. In order to persist any operations to an native "
"file system, you must call"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:106
msgid ""
"// nativefs is the returned from: await pyodide.mountNativeFS('/mount_dir', "
"dirHandle)\n"
"pyodide.runPython(`\n"
"  with open('/mount_dir/new_file.txt', 'w') as f:\n"
"    f.write(\"hello\");\n"
"`);\n"
"\n"
"// new_file.txt does not exist in native file system\n"
"\n"
"await nativefs.syncfs();\n"
"\n"
"// new_file.txt will now exist in native file system\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:120
msgid "or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../usage/file-system.md:122
msgid "pyodide.FS.syncfs(false, callback_func);\n"
msgstr ""
